the type C connector which is meant to replace many peripheral connections.

45
00:02:58,165 --> 00:03:03,115
It's quickly becoming a universal standard for display and data transfer.

46
00:03:03,115 --> 00:03:04,875
In addition to USB peripherals,

47
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:07,870
you should also be aware of display peripherals.

48
00:03:07,870 --> 00:03:10,270
There are some common inputs standards to know.

49
00:03:10,270 --> 00:03:13,810
Most computer monitors will have one or more of these connections,

50
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:16,255
but you might encounter some older standards too.

51
00:03:16,255 --> 00:03:20,565
DVI. DVI cables generally just output video.

52
00:03:20,565 --> 00:03:22,980
If you need to hook up a monitor or projector for

53
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:26,990
a slide presentation and you want audio too, you may be out of luck.

54
00:03:26,990 --> 00:03:30,610
Instead, you want to look at one of the following cables.

55
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:34,230
HDMI. This has become a standard in lots of televisions

56
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:38,660
and computers nowadays and outputs both video and audio.

57
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:41,580
Another standard that's become popular among manufacturers is

58
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:45,930
a displayPort which also outputs audio and video.

59
